# Project context (StreamMyCourse)

Before **planning or implementing** non-trivial changes in this repository (features, APIs, infra, or cross-cutting refactors):

1. Read **`AGENTS.md`** at the repository root.
2. Load the documents it points to as needed for the task—at minimum **`design.md`** (MVP contract and APIs) and **`roadmap.md`** when scope touches post-MVP or priorities; use **`ImplementationHistory.md`** and **`plans/architecture/`** when behavior or past decisions matter.

If the user explicitly limits scope (“doc-only”, “typo in X”), skip full context. For ambiguous requests, prefer loading **`design.md`** first so work stays aligned with the MVP.
